To be healthy, it's important to maintain a balanced diet, exercise regularly, and get enough sleep. Incorporate a variety of fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and lean proteins into your diet. Engage in at least 30 minutes of moderate physical activity most days of the week. Aim for 7-9 hours of sleep per night. Avoid smoking and excessive alcohol consumption. Regular health check-ups are also important to identify any potential health issues early on.